(309, 1, '2024-08-29 04:04:25', '2024-08-29 04:04:25', '[et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" fullwidth=\"on\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_fullwidth_slider _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_slide heading=\"About the Project\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" header_text_align=\"left\" background_enable_color=\"off\" background_video_mp4=\"http://localhost/enmaps/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/1-01-CoralsandFishes_StockVideo-1.mp4\" background_enable_video_mp4=\"on\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" sticky_transition=\"on\"][/et_pb_slide][/et_pb_fullwidth_slider][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_row column_structure=\"3_5,2_5\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_column type=\"3_5\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The project </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Effectively Managing Networks of Marine Protected Areas in Large Marine Ecosystems in the ASEAN Region </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(ASEAN ENMAPS) is a five-year project implemented by the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) through the funding of the Global Environment Facility (GEF), and with the ASEAN Centre for Biodiversity (ACB) as the executing agency.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It aims to improve the management of marine protected areas (MPAs) in four Large Marine Ecosystems (LMEs) in the ASEAN region (i.e. Bay of Bengal, Indonesian Seas, South China Sea, and Sulu-Celebes Sea) by building on national initiatives and using integrated coastal management (ICM) and marine spatial planning (MSP) to expand marine corridor protection. These approaches will enable the target LMEs to support sustainable fisheries and ecosystem services.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The project will run from March 2028 to March 2029 in 11 pilot sites within the three participating countries of Indonesia, the Philippines, and Thailand.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"2_5\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The ASEAN region is home to a third of the worlds coastal and marine habitats, providing fisheries with breeding, nursing, and feeding grounds.</span></i></p>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite their importance, these rich ecosystems face threats due to unsustainable resource use, habitat change, pollution, policy gaps, and the pressures of population growth and over exploitation, which heighten resource demands.</span></i></p>\n<p><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ASEAN ENMAPS is designed to address the threats facing the coastal and marine environment in the ASEAN region by facilitating transformative changes in the management of MPAs and other coastal and marine resources in the ASEAN Large Marine Ecosystems.</span></i></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" custom_margin=\"0px||0px||true|false\" custom_padding=\"0px||0px||true|false\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_row column_structure=\"1_2,1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" width=\"100%\" max_width=\"1996px\" custom_margin=\"0px|0px|0px|0px|true|true\" custom_padding=\"0px|0px|0px|0px|true|true\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" custom_padding=\"65px|65px|65px|65px|true|true\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<h2><b>Project Objective</b></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To develop and improve the management of MPANs and marine corridors within selected LMEs in the ASEAN region for the conservation of globally significant biodiversity and support for sustainable fisheries and other ecosystem goods and services</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_image src=\"http://localhost/enmaps/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bg1.jpg\" title_text=\"bg1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" hover_enabled=\"0\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" custom_margin=\"0px|0px|0px|-30px|true|false\" custom_padding=\"0px|0px|0px|0px|true|true\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"][/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row column_structure=\"1_2,1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" width=\"100%\" max_width=\"1996px\" custom_margin=\"0px||0px||true|false\" custom_padding=\"0px||0px||true|false\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_image src=\"http://localhost/enmaps/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bg1.jpg\" title_text=\"bg1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" hover_enabled=\"0\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" custom_margin=\"|-55px|||false|false\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"][/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" custom_padding=\"65px|65px|65px|65px|true|true\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<h2><b>Project Results-Based Framework</b></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Efforts to promote conservation through integrated coastal management, and marine spatial planning are progressing in the ASEAN region in terms of policy, planning, and implementation. However, effective multi-stakeholder collaboration remains a challenge, which hinders the realisation of these conservation investments.</span></p>\n<p><b><i>Barriers and causal pathways</i></b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The project baseline is marked by a lack of understanding of coastal and marine ecosystems, insufficient investment in MPA management, governance and financial issues, limited capacity for integrated approaches, and inadequate sharing of knowledge and best practices.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ASEAN ENMAPS Theory of Change highlights the causal pathways that the project will implement to move towards the GEF alternative scenario and achieve long-term outcomes: strengthened Blue Economy through integrated marine ecosystem management, achieving management goals, enhancing local community well-being through participatory approaches, reducing threats to coastal and marine ecosystems, and sharing knowledge for regional collaboration and replication across ASEAN Member States.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<h2><b>Project Information</b></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ASEAN ENMAPS is designed to address the threats facing the coastal and marine environment in the ASEAN region by facilitating transformative changes in the management of MPAs and other coastal and marine resources in ASEAN LMEs. The project strategy has a strong upscaling focus as it engages with ASEAN working groups and LME cooperative governance, while leveraging complementary investments across the region.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.25.0\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_font=\"Urbanist||||||||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\"]<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Participating Countries</b></td>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Republic of Indonesia</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Republic of the Philippines</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kingdom of Thailand</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Funding Agency</b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">GEF</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Implementing Agency</b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UNDP Bangkok Regional Hub</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Executing Agency</b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ACB</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>National Executing Partners</b></td>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ministry of Environment and Forestry (Indonesia)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Department of Environment and Natural Resources (Philippines)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Office of Natural Resources and Environmental Policy and Planning (Thailand)</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Project Duration</b></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">March 2024 to March 2029</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Total Budget</b></td>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">GEF Investment: USD 12,548,861</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Co-financing: USD 57,907,646</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '48-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-08-29 04:04:25', '2024-08-29 04:04:25