(418, 1, '2024-09-02 06:58:32', '2024-09-02 06:58:32', '[et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.16\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" theme_builder_area=\"initial_post_content\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.16\" background_size=\"initial\" background_position=\"top_left\" background_repeat=\"repeat\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" theme_builder_area=\"initial_post_content\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.16\" custom_padding=\"|||\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" custom_padding__hover=\"|||\" theme_builder_area=\"initial_post_content\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.16\" background_size=\"initial\" background_position=\"top_left\" background_repeat=\"repeat\" global_colors_info=\"{}\" theme_builder_area=\"initial_post_content\"]<!-- divi:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\">ADPLS is located on the eastern side ofLingayen Gulf,along the coastal areas of the municipalities of Agoo, Sto. Tomas, and Rosario in southernLa Union, Philippines.<br>ADPLS has a total area of 10,774.68 ha, with a marine area cover of 10,564.68 ha (98%), terrestrial area of 210ha (2%), and with approximately 26.4 km combined coastline of the three municipalities. ADPLS has a Strict Protection Zone/Habitat Conservation/Restoration Zone of 2,253.34 ha (20.91%) and a Multiple Use Zone of 8,521.34 ha (79.09%).<br>The marine ecosystems in the ADPLS include 18.72 ha of mangrove stands (7 species), 30.24 ha of seagrass beds (5 species), 1.2 hectares of artificial reefs, and stretches of fine black sand beaches covering approximately 30 km of coastline.<br>ADPLS also hosts numerous faunal assemblages consisting of economically important finfishes (39 species), invertebrates, and birds. Other high-value species are grouper, snapper, seabass, siganid (rabbitfishes), silver pompano, etc.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /divi:table -->[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Agoo-Damortis Protec